<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 20-SI SERIES, TYPE 300 (BRUSHLESS) - TROUBLESHOOTING - RATED VOLTAGE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="1">
        <title>RATED VOLTAGE</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Preferably alternator output should be checked at the "Rated Voltage" given in
                <hotlnk xrefid="hl0801304">Table 1</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <para>However, it is permissible to check the output in amperes at any voltage within the "Operating Range"
                listed in the table, since the current output will be quite close to the value that would be obtained at
                "Rated Voltage." The voltage should never be allowed to rise above the "Operating Range" for any length
                of time.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Table 1</title>
            <table id="hl0801304">
                <title>Voltage Operating Range Table</title>
                <tgroup cols="3">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.50in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>System Voltage</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Rated Voltage</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Operating Range (Voltage)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>12</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>14</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>13 - 15</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <para>It should be noted that the voltage may be below the "Operating Range" if the battery is in a low
                state of charge. However, as the battery receives a charge, the voltage will rise to some value within
                the "Operating Range."
            </para>
            <para>Operation of the charging system should be checked in the vehicle as follows:</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insure that an undercharged condition has not been caused by accessories having been
                    left on for extended periods.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check the drive belt for proper tension.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If a battery defect is suspected, check battery as instructed in the GROUP 08, BATTERY
                    section of the Service Manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the wiring for defects. Check all connections for tightness and cleanliness,
                    including the battery cable clamps and posts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect a voltmeter from "POS" terminal on alternator to ground. A zero reading
                    indicates an open between voltmeter connection and battery.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With all accessories turned off, increase engine speed as required to obtain maximum
                    voltage reading.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If voltage exceeds 15 volts on a 12-volt system, remove alternator for repair.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If previous Steps 1 through 7 check out OK then check the alternator as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Disconnect battery ground cable.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Connect an ammeter in the circuit at the "POS" terminal of the alternator (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0801305">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="f0801305" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="g0801305" filename="../figg08/g0801305.png" type="png" resolution="72"/>
                        <caption>Output Check</caption>
                        <calloutgroup>
                            <callout1>1. ALTERNATOR</callout1>
                            <callout1>2. "POS" (OUTPUT) TERMINAL</callout1>
                            <callout1>3. TEST AMMETER</callout1>
                            <callout1>4. CARBON PILE</callout1>
                            <callout1>5. BATTERY</callout1>
                            <callout1>6. TEST VOLTMETER</callout1>
                        </calloutgroup>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Reconnect battery ground cable.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Connect carbon pile and test voltmeter across battery (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f0801305">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">With accessories turned "ON" operate engine at moderate speed as required, usually
                        4000 alternator rpm or more. Adjust carbon pile as required to obtain maximum current output.
                    </para>
                    <specpara>
                        <important>
                            <para>Initial voltage build-up is by residual magnetism in the rotor. Increase the speed as
                                required to obtain maximum current output.
                            </para>
                        </important>
                    </specpara>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If current output is within 10 amperes of rated output as stamped on alternator
                        frames, alternator is not defective.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If ampere output is not within 10 amperes of rated output as stamped on alternator
                        frame, remove the alternator for repair.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
